This paper deals with knowledge graph completion, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) since it uses textual descriptions of entities to make predictions. The paper proposes a novel model that combines different embeddings, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) since it deals with predicting missing links in a knowledge graph. Finally, the paper uses several datasets, which are commonly used in database research (cs.DB).
